MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-13 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector. Specialized experience must demonstrate the following: 1. Using advanced HR principles and comprehensive classification principles, concepts, practices and procedures; 2. Conducting reviews and analyzing position management and classification program operations to include identifying deficiencies and measuring compliance, consistency, and effectiveness;
3. Providing written classification services to include structuring highly technical organizations/positions for mass reorganizations and realignments, providing classification metrics/reports, providing classification evaluation statements, providing documentation for classification audits and advisories; and
4. Classifying positions for organizations that are complex and dynamic. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management web site: https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series Experience refers to paid and unpaid experience, including volunteer work done through National Service programs (e.g., professional, philanthropic, religious, spiritual, community, student, social). Volunteer work helps build critical competencies, knowledge, and skills and can provide valuable training and experience that translates directly to paid employment.
